61555319203975.message: Inbreeding can have several effects on populations, including reduced genetic diversity and increased expression of harmful recessive traits. When closely related individuals breed, there is a higher chance of offspring inheriting identical copies of harmful alleles from both parents, leading to genetic disorders or abnormalities. Additionally, inbreeding can decrease fertility and overall fitness in a population due to the accumulation of deleterious alleles. Over time, inbreeding can result in reduced adaptability to environmental changes and increased susceptibility to diseases. It's important for populations to maintain genetic diversity to ensure their long-term viability and resilience. ğŸ§¬
